# WhatsApp AI Platform — Backend Engine
### Claude-powered WhatsApp automation for Indian small businesses

---

## What this does

Every time a customer sends a WhatsApp message to a registered business:

1. Twilio receives the message and hits your webhook
2. Your server identifies which business it belongs to
3. Claude reads the business's data + full chat history
4. Claude generates an intelligent, contextual reply
5. Reply is sent back to the customer automatically
6. Everything is saved to the database for the dashboard

---

## File Structure

```
backend/
├── main.py              # FastAPI app + all REST APIs for dashboard
├── webhook.py           # WhatsApp message receiver + processing pipeline
├── claude_handler.py    # Claude AI integration (the brain)
├── database.py          # PostgreSQL models (Business, Contact, Message, Session)
├── requirements.txt     # Python dependencies
└── .env.example         # Copy this to .env and fill in your keys
```

---

## Setup Instructions

### Step 1 — Clone and install dependencies
```bash
cd backend
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### Step 2 — Set up environment variables
```bash
cp .env.example .env
# Now open .env and fill in all values
```

### Step 3 — Set up database
For development, SQLite is used automatically (no setup needed).
For production, create a PostgreSQL database and update DATABASE_URL in .env.

### Step 4 — Run the server
```bash
uvicorn main:app --reload --port 8000
```

Server runs at: http://localhost:8000
API docs at:    http://localhost:8000/docs   ← Swagger UI, very useful!

### Step 5 — Expose to internet (for Twilio webhook)
Twilio needs to reach your server. Use ngrok for development:
```bash
# Install ngrok from ngrok.com, then:
ngrok http 8000
# You'll get a URL like: https://abc123.ngrok.io
```

### Step 6 — Configure Twilio
1. Go to https://console.twilio.com
2. WhatsApp → Sandbox Settings
3. Set webhook URL to: https://abc123.ngrok.io/webhook/whatsapp
4. Method: POST
5. Save

### Step 7 — Register your first business
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/api/businesses \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "name": "Ravi Tiles Hyderabad",
    "whatsapp_number": "+919876543210",
    "business_type": "tiles",
    "owner_name": "Ravi",
    "owner_phone": "+919876543211",
    "bot_config": {
      "business_description": "We sell floor tiles, wall tiles, bathroom fittings and outdoor tiles in Hyderabad. We have been in business for 10 years.",
      "services": ["Floor tiles", "Wall tiles", "Bathroom fittings", "Outdoor tiles"],
      "price_range": "₹28 to ₹150 per square foot depending on type and quality",
      "working_hours": "Monday to Saturday, 9am to 7pm",
      "location": "Kukatpally, Hyderabad",
      "delivery": "We deliver across Hyderabad within 3 to 5 working days",
      "faqs": [
        {"q": "Do you give samples?", "a": "Yes, free samples available for orders above 100 sqft"},
        {"q": "What is minimum order?", "a": "Minimum order is 50 square feet"},
        {"q": "Do you install tiles?", "a": "Yes, we provide installation service at extra cost"}
      ],
      "escalation_keywords": ["complaint", "refund", "damage", "wrong tiles", "speak to owner"],
      "language_preference": "auto"
    }
  }'
```

Now send a WhatsApp message to your Twilio sandbox number — Claude will reply!

---

## API Reference

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| POST | /webhook/whatsapp | Twilio webhook (auto-called) |
| POST | /api/businesses | Register new business |
| GET | /api/businesses/{id} | Get business profile |
| PUT | /api/businesses/{id}/config | Update bot config |
| GET | /api/businesses/{id}/conversations | All contacts + last message |
| GET | /api/businesses/{id}/contacts/{cid}/messages | Full chat history |
| GET | /api/businesses/{id}/analytics | Key metrics |
| POST | /api/ai/generate-faqs | Auto-generate FAQs (Claude) |
| POST | /api/ai/draft-broadcast | Draft broadcast message (Claude) |
| POST | /webhook/resume-bot/{bid}/{phone} | Resume bot after human handoff |

Full interactive docs: http://localhost:8000/docs

---

## What Claude does in this platform

| Feature | How Claude is used |
|---------|-------------------|
| Customer chat replies | Reads business data + history, replies intelligently |
| Language detection | Auto-replies in Telugu, Hindi, or English |
| Escalation detection | Identifies frustrated customers, alerts owner |
| FAQ generation | Generates 8 FAQs from a business description |
| Broadcast drafting | Writes WhatsApp campaigns from a goal |

